      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TIZ WORTHY (7) presents third up and ready to fire. Things didn't work out fresh in a stronger race at Flemington  but she was good to the line at Caulfield Heath last time in a handy BM66. With clear running from the inside gate she'll be very hard to hold out. YAMASHITA'S GOLD (5) ran a solid race fresh behind a talented horse in Tower Of Bridge, well backed on that occasion too. He'll be fitter for that and take beating. SYMPHONY OF COLOUR (4) ran an improved race second up at Cranbourne over 955m when getting into third late. Fancy this track will suit better and she should be hard to hold out. STEAMY MIST (9) resumes. Her form dropped off before a spell but the fresh run was good and she's jumped out well. COMMANDS SUCCESS (1) is racing well without winning this time in and has each way claims again.",
